{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"2a2f20a5-7cb5-4dbc-973c-f2d1965d2cb7","content":"Here's what you need to change:\n\n1. **Update NuGet packages:**\n   - Update `NUnit3TestAdapter` to **v5.0.0+** (it bundles the MTP integration).\n   - Remove `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` — it's for VSTest only.\n\n2. **Add the MTP package:**\n   ```xml\n   <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.NUnit\" Version=\"1.*\" />\n   ```\n\n3. **Enable MTP in your project file:**\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n4. **Run tests** the same way:\n   ```bash\n   dotnet test\n   ```\n\n> **Note:** With MTP, each test project becomes its own executable. If you used `.runsettings` or custom VSTest adapters, review the [Microsoft.Testing.Platform docs](https://learn.microsoft.com/dotnet/core/testing/microsoft-testing-platform-overview) for equivalent configuration.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"52d331c1-22b4-4044-a244-102ff8b9dfb4","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating an NUnit test project from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. This is a knowledge question - I don't need to search any codebase. Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":333,"requestId":"3411:371ABE:72C8D2B:7F1F398:69F3FA7F"},"id":"f0cdd0ad-7002-42c1-be46-5ec2f6967fd3","timestamp":"2026-05-01T00:57:44.128Z","parentId":"6aaa872f-955e-47d1-8fdd-09bb36d5b4f0"}
